name: Granny’s Mini Pecan Pies
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, cut into pieces and chilled'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '7', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ice-cold water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pecan halves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light corn syrup'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'vanilla ice cream, for serving'}
steps: Pulse 2 1/2 cups flour, chilled butter pieces, and salt in a food processor until mixture resembles coarse crumbs, about 10 pulses. Stir together ice-cold water and cider vinegar in a small bowl. Pour half ice water mixture into flour mixture; pulse to combine, about 3 pulses. Pour remaining ice water mixture in a thin stream through opening in lid, adding just enough to moisten and pulsing just until mixture looks crumbly and starts to cling together.. Turn out dough onto a work surface and pat into a circle; divide in half. Form each half into a disc; wrap each disc in plastic wrap. Chill at least 30 minutes.. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (180 degrees C).. Turn chilled dough out onto a lightly floured surface. Roll out dough to 2 (12-inch) rounds. Trace around a 6-inch plate with a paring knife to get 5 (6-inch) rounds total, rerolling scraps as needed. Transfer dough rounds to 5 (4- to 4 1/2-inch) pie pans, lightly pressing into pans. Crimp edges as desired. Arrange pecan halves in bottom of each crust. Transfer pie pans to a baking sheet.. Whisk together sugar, the 2 tablespoons flour, and nutmeg in a medium bowl. Whisk in eggs, corn syrup, the 1/2 cup water, melted butter, and vanilla until smooth. Stir in chopped pecans. Divide mixture evenly among pie crusts.. Bake in the preheated oven until centers are set but slightly wobbly, 50 to 60 minutes. Cool completely on wire racks. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

name: Mini Pecan Pies

steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Place pecans on a food processor and pulse until coarsely chopped.. Mix sugar, eggs, light corn syrup, dark corn syrup, butter, vanilla extract, and salt together in a bowl; fold in pecans. Spoon 1/4 cup pecan mixture into each mini pie shell. Transfer pies onto a baking sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until mini pies are slightly browned, 25 to 30 minutes. Serve warm or cool and place in airtight containers for up to one week.

name: Pecan Pumpkin Pie
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'solid pack pumpkin puree'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'sweetened condensed milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pie crust', 'name': 'pie crust'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'orange zest'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pecan halves'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (230 degrees C).. Combine eggs, sugars, flour, spices, and salt in a large bowl. Blend in pumpkin. Gradually add condensed milk; mix until well combined. Pour into prepared pie crust.. Bake pie in the preheated oven for 10 minutes. Meanwhile make the topping: Combine 2 tablespoons butter, 1 tablespoon grated orange rind, 1/4 cup brown sugar, and 3/4 cup whole pecans.. Reduce heat to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) and continue to bake pie until filling is set, about 40 to 50 minutes longer. Top pie with pecan mixture 10 minutes before removing from the oven.

name: Chocolate Bourbon Pecan Pie

Reduce heat to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C), and continue baking until pie is golden brown and slightly puffed on top, about 35 to 40 minutes.

name: Pecan Pie Cheesecake
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'crushed graham crackers'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely chopped toasted pecans'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'granulated sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '(8 ounce) packages', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'packed light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'dark rum'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1 ¾', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'coarsely chopped toasted pecans'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spray a 9-inch springform pan with cooking spray; line bottom with a round of parchment paper, and wrap outside of pan with heavy duty aluminum foil. To make the crust: Combine graham cracker crumbs, pecans, sugar, cinnamon, and salt for the crust in a bowl. Stir in melted butter until mixture has a sand-like consistency.. Press crumb mixture evenly into the bottom and up the sides of the prepared pan using a flat-bottomed measuring cup or your fingers.. Bake in the preheated oven on the center oven rack until lightly browned and fragrant, about 10 minutes. Remove from oven and cool on a wire rack for 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C), and place oven rack in lower third position.. Meanwhile, make the cheesecake filling: Combine cream cheese and brown sugar in a food processor and process until smooth and no lumps remain, about 45 seconds, scraping down sides as needed. Add eggs, 1 at a time, pulsing once after each addition. Add sour cream, flour, vanilla, cinnamon, and salt; pulse 2 to 3 times or until combined. Pour batter into cooled crust.. Bake cheesecake in the hot oven at 325 degrees F (165 degrees C) on rack in lower third position until center jiggles slightly, 45 to 50 minutes. Turn oven off, prop oven door open slightly, and let cheesecake stand in oven 1 hour. Remove from oven, discard foil, and run a knife around around edge of crust to release from pan (to avoid cracks while cooling). Cover with plastic wrap, and chill at least 6 hours or overnight.. To make the pecan pie topping: Set a a medium nonstick saucepan over low heat. Add sugar in an even layer and cook over low, undisturbed, until warm, about 2 minutes. Add water, and stir constantly until all the sugar is melted, about 45 seconds. Add butter, stirring constantly until butter is melted and incorporated, about 30 seconds.. Increase heat to medium; add heavy cream, rum, cinnamon, and vanilla, and cook, stirring constantly, until well combined and slightly thickened, about 2 minutes. Add pecans, stirring until well coated, and remove from heat. Cool until room temperature and thickened, about 30 minutes.. Remove cheesecake from the refrigerator, and carefully remove from springform pan. Place on a serving platter, and top with cooled pecan pie topping. Serve immediately, or allow cheesecake to soften for 15 minutes before serving.

name: Pecan Tarts
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.1 ounce) package', 'name': 'double-crust pie pastry, thawed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'dark corn syrup'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Lightly grease eight 3-inch tart tins.. Roll out pastry and cut out eight 5-inch circles; fit pastry circles into greased tart tins.. Mix sugar, eggs, corn syrup, melted butter, and vanilla extract in a large bowl until combined; stir in pecans. Spoon filling into each pastry-lined tart tin, filling each 3/4 full.. Bake in the preheated oven until pastry is golden brown and filling is set, about 30 to 35 minutes.

name: Irresistible Pecan Pie
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, chilled'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ice water'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light corn syrup'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'dark corn syrup'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pecans, finely crushed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pecans, quartered'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pecan halves'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. To Make Crust: In a medium bowl, combine flour, salt and white sugar. Cut butter into flour mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs. Gradually sprinkle the water over the dry mixture, stirring until dough comes together enough to form a ball.. On a floured surface flatten dough ball with rolling pin. Roll out into a circle that is one inch larger than pie dish. Place pie shell into dish and refrigerate until pie filling is complete.. To Make Pie Filling: In a medium bowl, mix together eggs, light and dark corn syrups, brown sugar, butter, salt and finely crushed pecans. Spread quartered pecans over bottom of refrigerated pie crust. Pour syrup mixture over top of pecans, then arrange pecan halves on top of pie.. Bake in a preheated 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) oven for one hour or until firm; let cool for one hour before serving.

name: Sweet Potato Pecan Pie
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(9 inch)', 'name': 'unbaked pie crust'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked and mashed sweet potatoes'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '1 ⅔', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'light cream'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '⅔', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Bake sweet potatoes until fork-tender, 40 to 50 minutes. Cool until easily handled.. Peel and mash sweet potatoes. Make sure all lumps are removed, straining if necessary.. Lightly beat eggs. Blend together eggs and sweet potatoes. Stir in sugar, salt, cinnamon, ginger, and cloves. Blend in cream. Pour into pie shell.. Bake in the preheated oven for 45 to 55 minutes, or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge of pie comes out clean. Cool completely on a rack.. Make the caramelized pecan topping. Combine butter or margarine, brown sugar, and pecans. Gently drop by spoonfuls over cooled pie to cover top. Broil 5 inches below heat until mixture begins to bubble, about 3 minutes. Watch carefully, if cooked too long, top will turn syrupy. Cool on rack.

name: Pecan Pie Tarts
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1 ¾', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}
steps: Preheat oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C).. Grease 30 tart tins or muffin cups and set aside.. To Make Crust: In a medium mixing bowl cream together cream cheese and 1 cup butter until light and fluffy. Blend in flour, 1/2 cup at a time, forming a smooth dough. Roll into 30 equal balls and press one into each greased tin so it lines the bottom and sides, like a pie crust.. To Make Filling: In a medium mixing bowl cream together 1/4 cup butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat in eggs and vanilla until thoroughly blended. Stir in pecans. Fill each lined tin half full. Mixture will rise as it bakes.. Bake in preheated oven for 25 minutes, or until lightly browned. Let cool in tins, then use the end of a table knife to flip each tart out of its tin.

name: Chocolate Pecan Delite
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'finely chopped pecans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "confectioners' sugar"}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'frozen whipped topping, thawed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3.9 ounce) package', 'name': 'instant chocolate pudding mix'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3.4 ounce) package', 'name': 'instant vanilla pudding mix'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. In a medium bowl, cut the butter into the flour with a pastry blender or two knives, until mixture resembles coarse meal. Stir in pecans, press into bottom of a 9x13-inch baking dish and bake 15 minutes, or until golden. Cool completely.. In a medium bowl, combine cream cheese, confectioners' sugar and 1 cup whipped topping with electric mixer until smooth. In a separate bowl, whisk together chocolate pudding mix, vanilla pudding mix and milk until there are no lumps. Combine cream cheese mixture and milk mixture and stir until smooth. Pour onto cooled crust. Spread remaining 2 cups of whipped topping on top of pudding mixture. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons of chopped nuts over all. Chill in refrigerator until serving.

steps: Preheat the oven to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C). Spread pecans out on a cookie sheet.. Bake pecans in the preheated oven for 30 minutes, stirring halfway through. Continue to bake until toasted, checking and stirring every 15 minutes, for up to 30 more minutes. Remove from the oven and let cool completely.. Meanwhile, increase the oven temperature to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Whisk brown sugar, corn syrup, flour, butter, white sugar, eggs, bourbon, and vanilla together in a bowl until smooth. Fold in cooled pecan pieces and chocolate chips until combined. Pour mixture into pie crust.. Bake in the preheated oven until pie is set, 50 to 60 minutes. Serve warm or chilled.

name: Toasted Coconut, Pecan, and Caramel Pie
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(9 inch)', 'name': 'pie shells, baked'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'flaked coconut'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'sweetened condensed milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) container', 'name': 'frozen whipped topping, thawed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) jar', 'name': 'caramel ice cream topping'}
steps: In a medium skillet, melt butter or margarine over medium heat. Add coconut and pecans. Toss well, and saute until coconut is lightly browned. Set aside to cool.. In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy. Add condensed milk and mix until smooth. Fold in whipped topping. Spread 1/4 of cream cheese mixture into each pastry shell. Sprinkle 1/4 of coconut mixture over each pie. Drizzle 1/2 of caramel topping over each coconut layer. Follow with remaining cream cheese mixture, then remaining coconut mixture.. Pies may be served chilled or frozen.

name: Chef John's Pecan Pie
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'prepared pastry dough for 9-inch pie'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'pecan halves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light corn syrup'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'bourbon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'large eggs, whisked'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Roll pie dough in a 9 1/2-inch glass pie dish and crimp the edges. Cover dough in parchment paper and press paper down to line the dough; pour pie weights on top of the parchment paper and spread evenly over the bottom.. Bake in the preheated oven for 20 minutes. Remove parchment paper and pie weights to a bowl. Bake crust until lightly golden and set, about 10 minutes more.. Spread pecans out on a baking sheet. Bake in the oven until lightly toasted, 7 to 8 minutes.. Stir brown sugar, butter, white sugar, corn syrup, flour, milk, bourbon, vanilla extract, and salt together in a saucepan over medium heat; bring to a boil, whisking constantly. Remove from heat and cool for 5 to 10 minutes.. Whisk eggs in a large bowl. Slowly drizzle sugar mixture into eggs, whisking constantly.. Spread pecans out in the bottom of the crust. Pour sugar mixture over nuts and gently stir with a spatula to coat all of the nuts.. Bake pie in the preheated oven until crust is golden brown and pie is set, 40 to 45 minutes. Cool completely.

name: Classic Pecan Pie
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Karo Light or Dark Corn Syrup'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pure vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': '(6 ounces) pecans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(9 inch)', 'name': 'unbaked deep dish pie crust'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Mix corn syrup, eggs, sugar, butter, and vanilla together in a large bowl using a spoon; stir in pecans. Pour into pie crust.. Bake in the preheated oven for 60 to 70 minutes. The pie is done when the center reaches 200 degrees F (95 degrees C). Tap the center surface of the pie lightly; it should spring back when done. If the pie crust is getting too brown, cover the edges with foil.. Cool for 2 hours before serving.

name: Upside-Down Apple Pecan Pie
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'firmly packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'margarine, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'pastry for a 9 inch double crust pie'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'Granny Smith apples - peeled, cored and sliced'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}
steps: Preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. In a 9 inch deep-dish pie pan, combine pecans, brown sugar and margarine; spread into a single layer. Roll out dough, and place bottom crust over pecan mixture.. In a large bowl, combine apples, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg. Pour into crust in pan. Top with second crust. Fold edges of crust over, and flute to seal edges. Make several small slits in the top to allow steam to escape.. Place pan on foil or cookie sheet during baking to guard against spillage. Bake in preheated oven for 40 to 50 minutes, or until crust is golden brown and apples are tender.. Cool pie in pan for 5 minutes. Place serving plate over pie, and flip to invert, being careful not to come in contact with molten sugar. If some of the nuts stick to the pan, remove them with a knife, and place on pie. Allow to cool for 1 hour.

name: Honey Crunch Pecan Pie
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shortening'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cold water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'distilled white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light corn syrup'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'bourbon (Optional)'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'packed brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'pecan halves'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. To Make Crust: In a medium bowl, mix together flour and 1 teaspoon salt. Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly. Gradually add water and vinegar. Cut together until mixture will hold together. Press dough into a ball and flour each side lightly. Wrap in plastic and chill for 20 minutes. Roll out between wax paper into a circle 1/8 inch thick and press into 9 inch pie pan.. To Make Filling: In a large bowl, combine eggs, 1/4 cup brown sugar, white sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt, corn syrup, melted butter, vanilla extract, and chopped pecans. Add bourbon if desired. Mix well. Spoon mixture into unbaked pie shell.. Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes. Remove and cover edges of pastry with aluminum foil. Return to oven for 20 minutes.. To Make Topping: Combine 1/3 cup brown sugar, butter or margarine, and honey in a medium saucepan. Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until sugar dissolves - about 2 minutes. Add pecans. Stir just until coated. Spoon topping evenly over pie.. Keep foil on edges of pastry and return pie to oven for an additional 10 to 20 minutes, until topping is bubbly and golden brown. Cool to room temperature before serving.

name: 8 Recipes for Pecan Pie Without Corn Syrup
Traditional Pecan Pie in a Jar

steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Spread pecans on a baking sheet.. Bake pecans in the preheated oven until lightly toasted, 6 to 8 minutes. Cool to room temperature.. Press pieces of pie crust dough into bottom and sides of jars. Add a layer of toasted pecans to each jar. Spoon in batter, leaving 1/4 inch rim at top.. Bake in preheated oven until darkened on the top, about 40 minutes. Cool to room temperature before serving.

name: Southern Pecan Pie Bars

steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a 9x13-inch baking pan with parchment paper, leaving a 2-inch overhang on at least 2 sides. Spray the parchment paper with baking spray.. Combine flour, butter, powdered sugar, and salt in a food processor and pulse 6 or 7 times to combine. name: Chocolate Pecan Pie II

name: Chocolate Pumpkin Pecan Pie
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'pumpkin puree'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'pumpkin pie spice'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': "semisweet chocolate (such as Baker's®), chopped"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'unsalted butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dark corn syrup (such as Karo®)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(9 inch)', 'name': 'deep-dish pie crust'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': '24 pecan halves (optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Mix pumpkin puree, eggs, sugar, cornstarch, vanilla extract, pumpkin pie spice, ginger, and salt in a large bowl until well combined. Set aside.. Place baking chocolate in a microwave-safe bowl. Microwave for 30 seconds, then stir. Continue to microwave chocolate at 30-second intervals until melted. Measure out 1 cup of pumpkin mixture and stir into chocolate mixture. Set aside.. Mix melted butter, brown sugar, dark corn syrup, egg, vanilla extract, and salt in a bowl until well combined. Stir in chopped pecans.. name: Pecan And Chocolate Espresso Pie
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter, chilled'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ice water'}, {'quantity': '1 ⅓', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'pecan halves'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'instant espresso powder'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsweetened cocoa powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light corn syrup'}
steps: To Make Crust: In a medium bowl, combine flour and salt and mix well. With two knives or a pastry blender, cut in butter until mixture is in fine crumbs. Gradually add just enough ice water so that the pastry holds together. Form into a ball, then flatten into a disk. Handle as little as possible. Wrap tightly in plastic wrap and chill for at least 1 to 2 hours.. Roll out crust on lightly floured surface with lightly floured rolling pin. Turn crust over frequently and lightly re-flour work surface and rolling pin as necessary. Crust should be rolled into a circle about 13 inches in diameter. Fit crust into an ungreased 9 inch pie plate of heatproof glass; form a high-standing rim, trimming excess from edges and pinching or fluting rim decoratively as desired.. Preheat oven to 400 degrees F (205 C). Thoroughly prick crust all over with fork. Chill for at least 10 minutes while oven heats. Bake in preheated oven 5 minutes (crust will not brown). Remove to rack and cool completely before filling.. Leave oven at 400 degrees F (205 C). Break up pecan pieces and sprinkle them evenly on the bottom of the cooled pie shell.. To Make Filling: In a small bowl beat eggs to combine. Add espresso powder and beat to mix. Let stand at least 10 minutes, beating occasionally to dissolve espresso.. In a medium bowl cream softened butter, sugar, and vanilla until light and fluffy. Beat in cocoa and salt. Add egg/espresso mixture 1/3 at a time, beating after each addition, until smooth. Stir in corn syrup. This mixture will be like custard and it will be thick.. Pour mixture slowly over pecans in pie shell. If any pecans do not get completely covered by the filling, submerge them until they do. Let stand 2 to 3 minutes; with toothpick or tip of sharp knife, pierce any remaining air bubbles (during this standing period, pecans may rise to top of pie).. Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes. Reduce heat from 400 degrees F (205 C) to 350 degrees F (175 C) and bake 33 to 37 minutes longer (or until edges are cracked and risen but pie center still quivers slightly when pie is shaken gently). Do not over-bake! If pie begins to brown excessively, cover top lightly with foil. Remove from oven; cool on rack before serving.

name: Pecan Chocolate Chip Pie
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, chilled and diced'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ice water'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light corn syrup'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'semisweet chocolate chips'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}

Add ice water and mix just until dough forms a ball.. Allow dough to rest in refrigerator for 20 minutes, then roll out and fit into a 9-inch pie plate. Set aside.. To Make Filling: In a medium bowl mix eggs and sugar. Add corn syrup and melted butter or margarine. Mix until all ingredients are thoroughly combined.. Spread chocolate chips and pecan pieces across bottom of pie shell. Pour egg mixture over chocolate chip and pecan layer.. Bake in preheated oven for 35 minutes. Serve warm or cool with a dollop of whipped cream and a sprinkling of chocolate chips if desired.

name: Maple Pecan Pie II
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter flavored shortening, chilled'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ice water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'distilled white vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg, beaten'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '', 'name': 'egg white'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '', 'name': 'eggs, beaten'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'real maple syrup'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light corn syrup'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dark corn syrup'}, {'quantity': '2 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1 ¼', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}, {'quantity': '⅓', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'maple syrup'}
steps: Sift together flour, 1 teaspoon salt and 1 teaspoon sugar into mixing bowl. Cut in shortening with a pastry blender until mixture resembles cornmeal. Brush inside of unbaked pie shell with slightly beaten egg white.. Mix 3/4 cup sugar, syrups, vanilla and salt with 4 beaten eggs until blended. Stir in pecans and melted butter. name: Pumpkin Tart with Pecan Crust
ingredients: {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pecan halves'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'rolled oats'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole wheat pastry flour'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'real maple syrup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy milk'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'arrowroot powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'pumpkin puree'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'real maple syrup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'grated fresh ginger'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly grated nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '⅛', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}
steps: Set rack in the middle of the oven, and preheat oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Lightly oil a 9 inch pie plate. Set aside.. Spread nuts over a baking pan. Toast for 7 to 10 minutes, or until the smell of nuts fills the kitchen. Set aside 16 pecan halves for garnish.. Combine oats, flour, remaining pecans, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon, and a pinch of salt in a food processor bowl. Pulse until mixture becomes a coarse meal. Transfer to a mixing bowl. Whisk together oil and 3 tablespoons maple syrup, and mix into dry ingredients to form a soft dough. Press mixture into prepared pie plate. Crimp edges. Bake for 10 minutes, and set aside to cool.. Blend soymilk and arrowroot in the food processor until the arrowroot is completely dissolved and the mixture is smooth, about 15 seconds. Add pumpkin, 1/2 cup maple syrup, ginger, 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon, 1/2 teaspoon salt, nutmeg, and cloves; process until thoroughly blended. Pour filling into baked crust, and smooth the top with a spatula.. Bake for about 35 minutes, or until the crust is lightly browned and the outside inch of the filling is set. Don't worry if the center is still soft; it firms up as the pie cools. Transfer pie to a wire the rack. Gently press toasted pecan halves into hot filling in 2 concentric circles. Cool to room temperature, and then chill until set, about 3 hours. Serve chilled or at room temperature.
